00:08:45,120 --> 00:08:48,159
RESUSCITATION BAY (SECTOR A)

97
00:08:57,360 --> 00:08:58,840
How did this happen?

98
00:09:00,800 --> 00:09:03,200
Actually, we were so close.

99
00:09:07,240 --> 00:09:08,480
The next time,

100
00:09:08,560 --> 00:09:11,640
we need to buy more
time no matter what.

101
00:09:12,120 --> 00:09:13,640
That way, no one gets hurt.

102
00:09:14,840 --> 00:09:16,200
There may not be the next time.

103
00:09:17,680 --> 00:09:19,320
Let's say saving
all the passengers

104
00:09:19,400 --> 00:09:21,320
is the key to breaking
out of the time loop.

105
00:09:22,080 --> 00:09:23,320
Well, we already did that.

106
00:09:24,640 --> 00:09:26,000
This is the last time.

107
00:09:32,960 --> 00:09:35,640
But I can't shake the feeling
that we haven't resolved anything.

108
00:09:38,000 --> 00:09:39,960
I feel like something
more happened

109
00:09:40,040 --> 00:09:42,080
after Wang Mengmeng's death.

110
00:09:45,600 --> 00:09:47,160
Look this up for me.

111
00:09:47,240 --> 00:09:49,400
"May 13th, 2014.

112
00:09:49,480 --> 00:09:51,280
River-crossing
bridge car accident.

113
00:09:52,000 --> 00:09:53,240
Route 45."

114
00:10:02,480 --> 00:10:03,520
Look at this.

115
00:10:06,840 --> 00:10:08,600
DO YOU THINK YOU'RE SPECIAL?

116
00:10:08,680 --> 00:10:10,000
SHE SHOULDN'T HAVE BEEN BORN

117
00:10:10,080 --> 00:10:11,280
SHE'S NOT RIGHT IN THE HEAD

118
00:10:11,360 --> 00:10:12,560
SCUM OF SOCIETY

119
00:10:12,640 --> 00:10:13,960
DIE!

120
00:10:14,040 --> 00:10:15,720
DOES SHE THINK THE
WORLD OWES HER?

121
00:10:15,800 --> 00:10:17,720
NICE DEATH!

122
00:10:17,800 --> 00:10:20,360
SHE MUST'VE BEEN SPOILED ROTTEN

123
00:10:36,480 --> 00:10:38,200
If Wang Mengmeng's parents

124
00:10:38,680 --> 00:10:40,200
see these comments,

125
00:10:41,480 --> 00:10:42,840
what will they think?

126
00:10:45,360 --> 00:10:46,400
Maybe

127
00:10:47,120 --> 00:10:49,080
for them,

128
00:10:49,640 --> 00:10:52,160
surviving isn't true salvation.

129
00:10:58,240 --> 00:11:01,360
We probably haven't gotten
to the heart of all this yet.

130
00:11:12,320 --> 00:11:16,880
TUESDAY, JIALIN
RIVER-CROSSING BRIDGE

131
00:11:16,960 --> 00:11:21,600
TUESDAY, JIALIN
RIVER-CROSSING BRIDGE

132
00:11:23,040 --> 00:11:24,840
After what happened
to Wang Mengmeng,

133
00:11:24,920 --> 00:11:26,800
Wang Xingde and Tao
Yinghong were dissatisfied

134
00:11:26,880 --> 00:11:28,280
with the
investigation's outcome.

135
00:11:28,360 --> 00:11:32,120
They also asked the police to investigate
why Wang Mengmeng got off the bus.

136
00:11:33,000 --> 00:11:34,960
Is the involved bus
driver here yet?

137
00:11:35,040 --> 00:11:35,960
He should be here soon.

138
00:11:36,040 --> 00:11:37,360
I'll receive him at the door.

139
00:11:42,120 --> 00:11:43,120
Mr. Qin.

140
00:11:43,640 --> 00:11:45,800
- Ms. Du.
- Thank you for coming, Mr. Qin.

141
00:11:46,880 --> 00:11:48,720
- Did you bring everything?
- Yes, I did.

142
00:11:48,800 --> 00:11:50,960
These are the statements,
accident reports,

143
00:11:51,040 --> 00:11:52,760
and all the related documents.

144
00:11:52,840 --> 00:11:54,480
This case wasn't
that complicated.

145
00:11:54,560 --> 00:11:55,920
There was nothing suspicious.

146
00:11:56,000 --> 00:11:57,760
It was just a traffic accident.

147
00:11:58,600 --> 00:11:59,600
Chain of evidence intact.

148
00:11:59,680 --> 00:12:00,880
The cause was clear.

149
00:12:00,960 --> 00:12:01,880
We determined that

150
00:12:01,960 --> 00:12:04,016
the bus driver who let her
out had primary liability.

151
00:12:04,040 --> 00:12:05,600
The dump truck had
secondary liability.

152
00:12:06,120 --> 00:12:07,800
Were there any problems
with compensation?

153
00:12:07,880 --> 00:12:09,040
There were none.

154
00:12:09,640 --> 00:12:11,520
The bus company paid
the compensation.

155
00:12:12,080 --> 00:12:13,760
The victim's family
didn't file a lawsuit.

156
00:12:13,800 --> 00:12:15,080
There was no financial dispute.

157
00:12:19,600 --> 00:12:20,640
Ms. Du.

158
00:12:22,680 --> 00:12:24,040
He is the one from the case.

159
00:12:24,120 --> 00:12:26,000
Mr. Zhu, the driver
of the Route 45 bus.

160
00:12:26,080 --> 00:12:27,640
Mr. Zhu, this is Ms. Du.

161
00:12:27,720 --> 00:12:28,960
Hello, Mr. Zhu.

162
00:12:29,040 --> 00:12:30,040
Have a seat.

163
00:12:30,480 --> 00:12:31,360
Come, sit down.

164
00:12:31,440 --> 00:12:32,920
- Sit down, Mr. Qin.
- Okay.

165
00:12:34,800 --> 00:12:36,400
Have a seat, Mr. Zhu.

166
00:12:38,120 --> 00:12:40,240
Don't be nervous, Mr. Zhu.

167
00:12:40,800 --> 00:12:43,560
We just want to learn more
from you about the situation.

168
00:12:43,640 --> 00:12:45,680
Just tell us the truth.

169
00:12:46,400 --> 00:12:48,040
We were watching this video.

170
00:12:48,120 --> 00:12:50,880
Wang Mengmeng was in a hurry
when she got off the bus.

171
00:12:51,400 --> 00:12:53,920
And she had arguments
and tussles with you.

172
00:12:54,480 --> 00:12:55,920
So what happened?

173
00:12:56,920 --> 00:12:59,560
It has already been five years.

174
00:13:00,400 --> 00:13:03,200
I've been asked all
the questions before.

175
00:13:04,440 --> 00:13:05,680
You are Mr. Qin

176
00:13:05,760 --> 00:13:07,480
from back then, right?

177
00:13:07,560 --> 00:13:08,480
Yes, it's me.

178
00:13:08,560 --> 00:13:11,520
Then you know better
than anyone else.

179
00:13:11,600 --> 00:13:13,040
You should talk to them.

180
00:13:13,120 --> 00:13:15,520
I answered all the
questions back then.

181
00:13:15,600 --> 00:13:17,360
- All I can do now is...
- Mr. Zhu.

182
00:13:18,000 --> 00:13:19,640
You've heard about the bombing.

183
00:13:20,240 --> 00:13:21,360
This is a serious case.

184
00:13:21,440 --> 00:13:22,520
Please cooperate.

185
00:13:33,200 --> 00:13:35,800
At the time, that young lady

186
00:13:36,280 --> 00:13:37,680
insisted on getting off.

187
00:13:38,400 --> 00:13:40,280
I really didn't expect this

188
00:13:40,360 --> 00:13:41,600
to happen.

189
00:13:42,240 --> 00:13:43,240
Otherwise,

190
00:13:43,280 --> 00:13:44,960
I wouldn't have let
her off the bus.

191
00:13:45,560 --> 00:13:47,640
But under the circumstances,

192
00:13:48,120 --> 00:13:49,760
I had no choice but
to drop her off.

193
00:13:50,560 --> 00:13:53,200
I'm sure you've all seen
the security footage.

194
00:13:53,280 --> 00:13:54,320
At the time,

195
00:13:54,400 --> 00:13:56,880
she was already
pulling on my arm.

196
00:13:56,960 --> 00:13:59,480
What if the bus was
steered off course?

197
00:13:59,560 --> 00:14:00,560
What would happen?

198
00:14:01,160 --> 00:14:03,160
The consequences
would be even worse.

199
00:14:03,240 --> 00:14:04,520
I'm a driver.

200
00:14:04,600 --> 00:14:07,920
I have to ensure the safety of
the dozens of passengers on board.

201
00:14:08,400 --> 00:14:10,440
If she had acted up

202
00:14:10,520 --> 00:14:11,920
anywhere else,

203
00:14:12,000 --> 00:14:14,120
I could have pulled
over for her.

204
00:14:14,880 --> 00:14:16,800
On the river-crossing bridge,

205
00:14:16,880 --> 00:14:18,200
there is no way.

206
00:14:18,280 --> 00:14:21,200
Didn't you think of asking
the passengers to stop her?

207
00:14:21,280 --> 00:14:23,480
No one on the bus helped.

208
00:14:25,880 --> 00:14:28,520
After the accident, did Wang
Mengmeng's parents contact you?

209
00:14:29,080 --> 00:14:30,920
Did they ask you why
Wang Mengmeng got off?

210
00:14:31,880 --> 00:14:33,320
Nothing in the world

211
00:14:33,400 --> 00:14:36,200
could make me brave enough
to talk to them face-to-face.

212
00:14:36,760 --> 00:14:40,000
I know that even if I were
to kneel and kowtow to them,

213
00:14:40,080 --> 00:14:41,360
they wouldn't accept it either.

214
00:14:42,360 --> 00:14:44,160
Especially that lady. She…

215
00:14:45,800 --> 00:14:47,160
Yes, I know.

216
00:14:48,520 --> 00:14:51,920
I breached the protocol.

217
00:14:53,280 --> 00:14:56,400
I know that I lost my
job because of this.

218
00:14:57,000 --> 00:14:58,480
I've admitted it myself.

219
00:15:03,080 --> 00:15:04,800
How much do you know
about the real reason

220
00:15:04,880 --> 00:15:05,960
that Wang Mengmeng got off?

221
00:15:06,560 --> 00:15:08,120
Or did she say anything to you?

222
00:15:09,200 --> 00:15:11,640
That young girl just
missed her stop.

223
00:15:11,720 --> 00:15:13,040
I've seen this

224
00:15:13,120 --> 00:15:14,640
more than a few times before.

225
00:15:14,720 --> 00:15:15,880
She kept babbling on and on.

226
00:15:15,960 --> 00:15:17,480
What she said didn't
make any sense.

227
00:15:17,560 --> 00:15:19,320
I didn't know what she wanted.

228
00:15:19,400 --> 00:15:21,320
She just kept wanting me
to stop and let her out.

229
00:15:21,400 --> 00:15:23,360
I was focused on the road.

230
00:15:23,440 --> 00:15:25,200
I didn't know what to do.

231
00:15:25,280 --> 00:15:26,680
It's the river-crossing bridge!

232
00:15:26,760 --> 00:15:28,400
You can't stop there!

233
00:15:28,480 --> 00:15:29,520
But you still stopped.

234
00:15:29,600 --> 00:15:31,040
Yes, I know I did stop!

235
00:15:31,120 --> 00:15:32,760
But what could I do?

236
00:15:32,840 --> 00:15:34,640
Five years have already passed!

237
00:15:34,720 --> 00:15:36,720
Why won't you let it go?

238
00:15:36,800 --> 00:15:39,040
Didn't you call me here
today to interrogate me?

239
00:15:39,120 --> 00:15:40,920
- No.
- Fine. Take me and execute me!

240
00:15:41,000 --> 00:15:42,256
- My life for hers!
- No, Mr. Zhu.

241
00:15:42,280 --> 00:15:43,560
- Mr. Zhu.
- Here.

242
00:15:43,640 --> 00:15:44,880
That's not our intention.

243
00:15:44,960 --> 00:15:46,160
Please have a seat.

244
00:15:46,240 --> 00:15:47,480
Mr. Zhu, calm down.

245
00:15:48,040 --> 00:15:49,080
Don't get so worked up.

246
00:15:49,160 --> 00:15:50,600
That's not our intention.

247
00:15:50,680 --> 00:15:51,680
We told you to come

248
00:15:51,760 --> 00:15:53,840
just to ask you to
think back carefully.

249
00:15:53,920 --> 00:15:55,920
Did you upset her parents

250
00:15:56,000 --> 00:15:57,600
to make them resent you?

251
00:15:57,680 --> 00:15:58,680
Resent?

252
00:16:00,280 --> 00:16:01,760
Who doesn't harbor resentment?

253
00:16:03,800 --> 00:16:05,720
I have resentment too.

254
00:16:14,320 --> 00:16:15,720
Okay, Mr. Zhu.

255
00:16:17,480 --> 00:16:18,720
Don't get worked up.

256
00:16:19,280 --> 00:16:20,280
Let's take a break.

257
00:16:20,360 --> 00:16:21,480
Here, Xiaoliu.

258
00:16:21,560 --> 00:16:23,400
Take Mr. Zhu to get
some tea and rest.

259
00:16:23,480 --> 00:16:24,840
- Come.
- Mr. Zhu.

260
00:16:24,920 --> 00:16:26,800
Here. Take a break.

261
00:16:41,000 --> 00:16:42,760
- Mrs. Zhang.
- Where is Zhang Cheng?

262
00:16:42,840 --> 00:16:44,600
I'm asking you. Where is he?

263
00:16:51,080 --> 00:16:54,160
We took a closer look at the
security cameras on the bus.

264
00:16:54,240 --> 00:16:56,160
We also talked to the
passengers on the bus.

265
00:16:56,240 --> 00:16:58,600
No one knows why Wang
Mengmeng got off the bus.

266
00:16:58,680 --> 00:16:59,720
We only found out that

267
00:16:59,800 --> 00:17:02,280
she seriously interfered
with the driver's driving.

268
00:17:02,360 --> 00:17:04,960
And aside from her frantic
hitting of the bus door,

269
00:17:05,040 --> 00:17:07,880
there was no proof that she
was in any physical danger.

